description.narrative: Output 2.4 Every Child learns: LAC COs have increased capacity to develop, implement and deliver results for every child to access ECD and education opportunities and learn, including in emergencies, fragile and humanitarian contexts., which contributes to Children With Disabilities, Early Childhood Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: OUTCOME 2 EVERY CHILD LEARNS : Girls and boys and adolescents in LAC benefit from equitable, inclusive and relevant ECD and education programmes and policies, fostering their full development in the early years, on-time enrollment, transitions, and completion as well as their learning and skills development.
